extremeDlcs.name: extremeDlcs
extremeDlcs.description: Extreme Dynamic-Link Context System (DLCS) status objects

extremeDlcsEnable.name: extremeDlcsEnable
extremeDlcsEnable.description: Setting this to true will allow the agent to start collecting DLCS binding information.

extremeDlcsNetbiosEnable.name: extremeDlcsNetbiosEnable
extremeDlcsNetbiosEnable.description: Setting this to true will allow the agent to start collecting DLCS binding information using the NetBios protocol.

extremeDlcsKerberos5Enable.name: extremeDlcsKerberos5Enable
extremeDlcsKerberos5Enable.description: Setting this to true will allow the agent to start collecting DLCS binding information using the Kerberos V5 protocol.

extremeDlcsRsvpEnable.name: extremeDlcsRsvpEnable
extremeDlcsRsvpEnable.description: Setting this to true will allow the agent to start collecting DLCS binding information using the RSVP protocol.

extremeDlcsDnsEnable.name: extremeDlcsDnsEnable
extremeDlcsDnsEnable.description: Setting this to true will allow the agent to start collecting DLCS binding information using the DNS protocol.

extremeDlcsBindingTable.name: extremeDlcsBindingTable
extremeDlcsBindingTable.description: Table of DLCS Binding information. Entries are added and deleted by the agent based on information gathered from the local network environment. Multiple entries may exist for almost identical sets of bindings although the agent will ensure that exactly matching entries are coalesced.

extremeDlcsBindingEntry.name: extremeDlcsBindingEntry
extremeDlcsBindingEntry.description: Entry in table of DLCS bindings.

extremeDlcsBindingIndex.name: extremeDlcsBindingIndex
extremeDlcsBindingIndex.description: An index into this table, chosen by the agent. This has no significance to the manager beyond its uniqueness within this agent.

extremeDlcsBindingType.name: extremeDlcsBindingType
extremeDlcsBindingType.description: The type of binding expressed here. A given bit is set if DLCS has detected that the two relevant items are bound together. e.g. an entry with application2user(3) set to 1 implies that the username extremeDlcsBindingUser has been seen to be using the application extremeDlcsBindingApplication. In addition, if this entry also has user2port(1) set to 1 then this user and application have been detected as running on the physical switch port extremeDlcsBindingPhysPort.

extremeDlcsBindingSource.name: extremeDlcsBindingSource
extremeDlcsBindingSource.description: The source of the information binding.

extremeDlcsBindingUser.name: extremeDlcsBindingUser
extremeDlcsBindingUser.description: The User name detected by DLCS. A string of length zero indicates no valid User name has been detected for this binding.

extremeDlcsBindingGroup.name: extremeDlcsBindingGroup
extremeDlcsBindingGroup.description: The Group name detected by DLCS. A string of length zero indicates no valid Group name has been detected for this binding.

extremeDlcsBindingApplication.name: extremeDlcsBindingApplication
extremeDlcsBindingApplication.description: The Application name detected by DLCS. A string of length zero indicates no valid Application name has been detected for this binding.

extremeDlcsBindingHost.name: extremeDlcsBindingHost
extremeDlcsBindingHost.description: The Host name detected by DLCS. A string of length zero indicates no valid Host name has been detected for this binding.

extremeDlcsBindingIpAddress.name: extremeDlcsBindingIpAddress
extremeDlcsBindingIpAddress.description: The IP address detected by DLCS. A value of 0.0.0.0 indicates no valid IP address has been detected for this binding.

extremeDlcsBindingPhysPort.name: extremeDlcsBindingPhysPort
extremeDlcsBindingPhysPort.description: The physical port number (ifIndex) detected by DLCS. This is valid in all bindings.

extremeDlcsBindingUpdateTime.name: extremeDlcsBindingUpdateTime
extremeDlcsBindingUpdateTime.description: The value of sysUpTime when this entry was last updated.
